value.snippet: Computers connected to a network are assigned a unique number known as Internet Protocol (IP) Address. IP (version 4) addresses consist of four numbers in the range 0-255 separated by periods (i.e. 127.0.0.1). A computer may have either a permanent (static) IP address, or one that is dynamically assigned/leased to it.
